  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance - Country-Level Funding - IOM 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to contribute to preventing, reducing, and mitigating serious protection threats for vulnerable populations who have been severely affected by the ongoing crisis, and by the recent outbreak of COVID-19 in South Sudan. This will be done through the provision of multi-sector life-saving humanitarian assistance. In particular, IOM is providing mental health and psychosocial support, gender based violence response, trafficking in persons response, and Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) support to internally displaced persons and vulnerable host communities across South Sudan.</narrative>
  </description>
